This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating captions for images. It also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it aims to generate captions that are more diverse and discriminative, which are important characteristics of human languages. The use of a generative adversarial network also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of comparative learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper may also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves generating captions that accurately describe images.
